<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF376A88FF5A94141B58B98F" pageId="204" pageNumber="966" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF376A88FF5A94141B58B98F" blockId="204.[162,1371,273,825]" pageId="204" pageNumber="966">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF376A88FF5A94141C07B95C" bold="true" box="[166,519,589,622]" pageId="204" pageNumber="966">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Annamit 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF376A88FEF8942D1F5EB9A7" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[260,350,628,661]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="204" pageNumber="966" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
is currently only known with certainty from two localities, although its distribution is probably wider. Virtually nothing is known about its ecology and threats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
